@startuml
title Secure Multi-Cloud Data Integrity and Self-Healing Storage System - Architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

actor "Authenticated User" as User

node "Client Browser" as Browser {
  component "Jinja HTML Pages\nlogin, signup, dashboard,\nintegrity, recovery, storage" as Pages
  component "static/js/app.js\nFetch API + UI rendering" as Frontend
  component "Bootstrap + styles.css" as UI
}

node "Flask Application Server" as FlaskServer {
  component "app.py\nFlask route/controller layer" as App
  component "Session Auth\nWerkzeug password hashing" as Auth
  component "MongoState\nMongoDB connection manager" as MongoState
  component "Integrity Helpers\nnormalize filenames,\nSHA-256 checks" as AppIntegrity
}

package "Service Layer" as Services {
  component "services.integrity\nverify_and_heal()\nsha256_bytes()\nutc_now()" as IntegrityService
  component "services.storage\nMultiCloudStorage" as StorageService
}

database "MongoDB Atlas" as Mongo {
  component "users" as UsersCollection
  component "files" as FilesCollection
  component "deleted_files" as DeletedFilesCollection
  component "recovery_logs" as RecoveryLogsCollection
}

cloud "Backblaze B2\nS3-Compatible API" as Backblaze {
  storage "Primary Bucket" as PrimaryBucket
  storage "Backup Bucket" as BackupBucket
}

User --> Pages : uses web UI
Pages --> Frontend : loads
Pages --> UI : styled by

Frontend --> App : HTTPS requests\n/api/me\n/api/files\n/api/upload\n/api/verify/{id}\n/api/delete/{id}\n/api/recover/{id}\n/api/view/{id}/{location}\n/api/download/{id}\n/api/recovery-logs
App --> Pages : renders server pages

App --> Auth : signup/login/logout\nsession checks
Auth --> UsersCollection : create user\nverify password hash

App --> MongoState : initialize DB client\nensure indexes
MongoState --> Mongo : TLS connection\nmongodb+srv

App --> AppIntegrity : filename normalization\nhash comparison\nstatus decisions
App --> IntegrityService : verify_and_heal(file, storage, db)
App --> StorageService : upload, view URL,\ndownload URL, delete,\nmanual recovery

IntegrityService --> StorageService : download primary/backup\noverwrite primary if valid backup exists
IntegrityService --> FilesCollection : update status + hashes
IntegrityService --> DeletedFilesCollection : update deleted metadata if needed
IntegrityService --> RecoveryLogsCollection : log tamper/recovery events

StorageService --> PrimaryBucket : upload/download/head/delete\npresigned URL
StorageService --> BackupBucket : upload/download/head\npresigned URL

App --> FilesCollection : create/list/update/delete active file metadata
App --> DeletedFilesCollection : soft-delete metadata\nrestore metadata
App --> RecoveryLogsCollection : insert/read recovery logs

note right of FilesCollection
Stores trusted original_hash,
current_hash, latest_hash,
object_name, status,
uploaded_by, timestamps.
end note

note bottom of Backblaze
The same object_name is stored in
both buckets. The backup bucket is
used to heal the primary copy.
end note

@enduml
